  "texts": [
    "The decoders in subsequent layers of the stack of N decoders process the output of the previous decoder.",
    "The last layer in the decoder stack produces the contextualized token matrix Z.",
    "The linear network at the output of the decoder stack converts the contextualized token vectors to logit vectors in matrix Y where the dimension of each vector is the length of the vocabulary indicated as m. GPT-3 uses m = 50,257 (Brown et al. 2020).",
    "The SoftMax function normalizes each logit value to a probability distribution (18) Z 0 = XW e + W p, Page 25 of 35 89 over the vocabulary.",
    "Therefore, the position of the peak value points to the position of the predicted next token in the vocabulary if the temperature setting is zero."
  ],
